TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lizzeri, Alessandro
AU  - Siniscalchi, Marciano
T1  - Parental Guidance and Supervised Learning*
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2008.123.3.1161
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 123
IS  - 3
SP  - 1161
EP  - 1195
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We propose a simple theoretical model of supervised learning that is potentially useful to interpret a number of empirical phenomena relevant to the nature-nurture debate. The model captures a basic trade-off between sheltering the child from the consequences of his mistakes and allowing him to learn from experience. We characterize the optimal parenting policy and its comparative-statics properties. We then show that key features of the optimal policy can be useful to interpret provocative findings from behavioral genetics.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2008.123.3.1161
ER  - 



